instruction:
The classic `for` loop gives you full control: start, condition, increment.

```js
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  // runs 5 times: i = 0, 1, 2, 3, 4
}
```

Run this. Then modify it to print only even numbers from 0 to 10.

`for...of` is the modern way to loop over arrays, strings, Maps, Sets — anything iterable.

Cleaner than classic `for` when you don't need the index:

```js
for (const name of names) {
  console.log(name);
}
```

